Female genitalia (Fig. 4
A-C
): tignum long, narrow, with central canal; posterior area broad, sclerotization poorly delineated; anterior area spatulate (Fig. 4B). Vaginal palpi elongate, basally strongly sclerotized, each with approximately eight setae at apex (Fig. 4C). Palpi rounded at apex, enlarged at last third but thinned at apex, situated close together and merged anteriorly for more than half of their length. Posterior sclerotization of vaginal palpi with convex sides. Spermatheca curved, with receptacle and pump not differentiated from each other. Apex of pump with spoon-like projection. Spermathecal duct long, widest at base, without coils (Fig. 4A).
